# EC2 Instance Storage Section

## what's an EBS Volume[块] ?

* An EBS （Elastic Block Store）Volume is a network drive you can attach [连接] to your instance while they run
* It allows your instances to persist [保留] data , even after their termination [终止]
* They can only be mounted to one instance at a time (at the CCP level)
* They are bound to specific availability zone [它们绑定到特定的可用区域]
* Analogy [比喻] ：Think of them as a "network USB stick"
* Free tier [免费套餐]: 30GB of free EBS storage of type General Purpose [通用型] (SSD) or Magnetic [磁性] per month
# EBS Volume

* it's a network drive (not a physical drive)
1.  it uses the network to communicate the instance ,which means there might be a bit of latency [延迟]
2. it can be detached [分离] from an EC2 instance and attached to another one quickly
* it's locked to an Availability Zone (AZ)
1. an EBS Volume in us-east-1a can't  be attached to us-east-1b
2. to move a volume across, you first need to snapshot [快照] it.
* have a provisioned capacity [有预配置的容量] (size in GBs, and IOPS)
1. you get billed for all the provisioned capacity [需要为所有的预配置付费]
2. you can increase the capacity of the drive over time [随着时间的推移，您可以增加驱动器的容量]
## Delete on Termination attribute [终止时删除属性]

![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* controls the EBS behaviour [行为] when an EC2 instance terminates
1.  by default ,the root EBS volume is deleted (attribute enabled)
2. by default,any other attached EBS volume is not deleted (attribute disabled)
* this can be controlled by the AWS console / AWS CLI
* Use case : preserve [保留] root volume when instance is terminated
# EBS Snapshots [快照]

* make a backup [备份] (snapshot) of your EBS volume at a point in time [在某个时间点]
* not necessary to detach [分离] volume to do snapshot , but recommended [推荐]
* can copy snapshots across AZ ( availability zone )or Region [地区]
## EBS snapshots features [特征]

* EBS Snapshots Archive [归档]
1. move a snapshot to an "archive tier" [归档层] that is 75% cheaper
2. takes within [..内]24 to 72 hours for restoring the archive [24 至 72 小时内恢复存档]
* Recycle Bin [回收站] for EBS Snapshots
1. setup rules to retain [保留] deleted snapshots so you can recover them after an accidental deletion.
2. specify retention [指定保留](from 1 day to 1 year)
* Fast Snapshots Restore (FSR)
1. force full initialization of snapshot  [快照完全初始化] to have no latency on the first use (expensive $$$)
# AMI Overview

* AMI = Amazon Machine Image [映像]
* AMI are a customization [定制] of an EC2 instance
1. you add your own software, configuration, operating system, monitoring [监控] ...
2. faster boot [启动]/ configuration time because all your software is pre-packaged
* AMI are built for a specific region (and can be copied across regions)
* you can launch EC2 instances from :
1. A public AMI : AWS provided
2. your own AMI : you make and maintain [维持] them yourself
3. an aws marketplace AMI : an AMI someone else made (and potentially sells [可能出售])
## AMI Process [流程](from an EC2 instance)

* start an EC2 instance and customize it
* stop the instance (for data integrity [为了数据完整性])
* build [构建] an AMI - this will also create EBS snapshots
* launch instance from other AMIs
# EC2 Instance Store

* EBS volumes are network drives with good but "limited" performance
* if you need a high-performance [高性能] hardware disk [磁盘], use EC2 instance store
* Better I/O performance
* EC2 Instance Store lose their storage if they're stopped (ephemeral [临时存储])
* good for buffer [缓冲]/ cache / scratch [暂存数据] data / temporary content [临时内容]
* risk of data loss if hardware fails 
* backups and replication are your responsibility [备份和复制是您的责任]
>IOPS : input / output ops [ Operations] per second
# *EBS Volume Types

* EBS Volumes come in 6 types
1. gp2/gp3 (SSD) : general purposing SSD volume that balance price and performance for a wide variety of workloads [通用 SSD 卷，可平衡各种工作负载的价格和性能]
2. io1 /io 2 Block Express (SSD) : highest-performance SSD volume for mission-critical [关键任务] low-latency or high-throughput workloads [适用于关键任务低延迟或高吞吐量工作负载的最高性能 SSD 卷]
3. st1 (HDD) : Low cost HDD volume designed for frequently accessed ,throughput-intensive workloads [低成本 HDD 卷，专为频繁访问、吞吐量密集型工作负载而设计]
4. sc1(HDD) : Lowest cost HDD volume designed for less frequently accessed workloads [成本最低的 HDD 卷，专为访问频率较低的工作负载而设计]
* EBS Volumes are characterized in size | throughput | IOPS
* when in doubt always consult the AWS documention - it's good
* **only gp2/gp3 and io1 / io2 Block Express can be used as boot [启动] volumes**
# EBS Volume Types Use cases

## *General purpose SSD

* gp2 : cost effetive storage, low-latency [低延迟，经济高效的的存储]
* system boot volumes ,virtual desktops, Development and test environments
* 1 GiB - 16 TiB
* gp3
1. baseline of 3000 IOPS and throughput of 125 MiB/s
2. can increase IOPS up to 16000 and throughput up to 1000 MiB/s independently [独立地]
* gp2
1. small gp2 volumes can burst IOPS to 3000
2. Size of the volume and IOPS are linked, max IOPS is 16000
3. 3 IOPS per GB, means at 5334 GB we are at the max IOPS
## *Provisioned [预配置 ] IOPS (PIOPS) SSD [固态硬盘]

* Critical business applications with sustained IOPS performance [具有维持IOPS 性能的关键业务应用程序]
* or applications that need more than 16000 IOPS
* Great for **databases workloads** (sensitive to storage perf and consistency [对存储性能和一致性敏感])
* io1 （4GiB - 16TiB）
1. **max PIOPS : 64000** for Nitro [自然] EC2 instance & 32000 for other
2. Can increase PIOPS independently from storage size [独立于存储大小来调配PIOPS]
* io2 Block Express(4GiB -64TiB)
1. sub-millisecond [亚毫秒级] latency
2. **max PIOPS : 256000** with an IOPS : GiB ratio of 1000 :1
* Supports EBS Multi-attach [支持EBS多连接]
## Hard Disk Drives (HDD) [硬盘驱动器]

* cannot be a boot volume [引导卷]
* 125 GiB to 16TiB
* throughput optimized HDD (st1)
1. big data, data warehouses [数据仓库], log processing
2. **max throughput** 500 MiB/s -max IOPS 500
* cold HDD (sc1) : 适用于归档的数据，不经常访问的数据
1. for data that is infrequently [很少] accessed
2. scenarios [场景] where lowest cost is important 
3. **max throughput** 250MiB/s- max IOPS 250
## EBS-Volume types summary

[https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ebs/latest/userguide/ebs-volume-types.html#solid-state-drives](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ebs/latest/userguide/ebs-volume-types.html#solid-state-drives)

# EBS multi-attach -io1/io2 family

* attach the same EBS volume to multiple EC2 instances in the same AZ
* each instance has full read & write permissions to the high-performance volume
* Use case :
1. achieve higher application availability in clustered [集群] Linux applications (ex. Teradata)
2. applications must manage concurrent write operations [并发写入操作]
* **up to 16 EC2 instance at a time**
* must use a file system that's cluster-aware [必须使用支持集群的文件系统] (not XFS,EXT4,etc....)
# Amazon EFS - Elastic File System

* managed NFS (network file system) that can be mounted on many EC2
* EFS works with EC2 instance in multi-AZ
* highly available , scalable [扩展性], expensive (3*gp2), pay per use
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* Use case：content management , web serving, data sharing , wordpress
* uses NFSv4.1 protocol
* uses security group to control access to EFS
* **compatible [兼容] with Linux based AMI (not window)**
* encryption at rest using KMS [使用KMS进行静态加密]
* POSIX file system (~Linux) that has a standard file API
* file system scales automatically [文件系统自动扩展], pay-per-use, no capacity planning [无需容量规划]!
## EFS - Performance & Storage Classes [存储类别]

### Performance

* **EFS Scale**
    *  1000s of concurrent NFS clients ,10 GB+ /s throughput [1000个并发NFS客户端，10GB+/s吞吐量]
    * grow to petabyte-scale network file system ,automatically [自动增长到PB级的文件系统]
* **performance mode (set at EFS creation time [****在 EFS 创建时设置****])**
    * **general purpose (default)**- latency-sensitive use cases(web server, CMS, etc../)
    * **Max I/O**- higher latency, throughput , highly parallel [高并发] (big data,  media processing)
* **throughput mode**
    * **Bursting** [突发]- 1TB = 50 MiB/s + burst of up to [突发高达]100MiB/s
    * **Provisioned [资源调配]**- set your throughput regardless [无论] of storage size, ex :1 GiB/s for 1TB storage.
    * **Elastic** - automatically scales throughput up or down based on your workloads 
        * up to 3GiB/s for read and 1GiB/s for writes
        * used for unpredicatable [不可预测的] workloads
### Storage Classes

* **Storage Tiers [存储层]（lifecycle management feature [生命周期管理功能] - move file after N days）**
    * standard : for frequently accessed files
    * infrequent [不常] access (EFS-IA) ：cost to retrieve files [检索文件成本], lower price to store . Enable EFS-IA with a lifecycle Policy [通过生命周期策略启用 EFS-IA]
![图片](data:image/png;base64,)


* **availability and durability [可用性和耐用性]**
    * standard : Multi-AZ, great for prod [生产环境]
    * one Zone : one AZ , great for dev ,backup enabled by default , compatible [兼容] with IA (EFS one zone-IA)
* over 90% in cost savings [节省成本 90% 以上]
# EBS vs EFS - Elastic Block Storage

## EBS Overview

* EBS  volumes
    * one instance (except multi-attach io1/io2)
    * are locked at the Availability Zone (AZ) level
    * gp2 : IO increase if the disk size increase
    * gps3 &io1 : can increase IO independently
* To migrate an EBS volume across AZ
    * take a snapshot
    * restore the snapshot to another AZ
    *  EBS backups use  IO and you shouldn't run them while your application is handling a lot of traffic
* Root EBS Volumes of instances get terminated by default if the EC2 instance gets terminated. (you can disable that) 
## EFS Overview

* Mounting 100s of instances across AZ [跨可用区安装数百个实例]
* EFS share website files (WordPress)
* Only for Linux Instances (POSIX)
* EFS has a higher price point than EBS
* Can leverage [可以利用] EFS-IA for cost savings
* Remember : EFS vs EBS vs Instance Store [EC2 Instance Store provides the best disk I/O performance.]
